## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="4746a-103">Il <xref:System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities> classe estende la <xref:System.Web.HttpBrowserCapabilities> classe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4746a-103">The <xref:System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities> class extends the <xref:System.Web.HttpBrowserCapabilities> class.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="4746a-104">Il <xref:System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities> classe offre un numero elevato di proprietà di sola lettura che forniscono accesso indipendente dai tipi al dizionario delle funzionalità dell'oggetto visualizzatore.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4746a-104">The <xref:System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities> class offers a large number of read-only properties that provide type-safe access to the Browser object's capabilities dictionary.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="4746a-105">È possibile utilizzare la proprietà di Browser del <xref:System.Web.HttpRequest> oggetto in modo che punti a un'istanza di un <xref:System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities> oggetto, che può quindi essere usato per leggere le funzionalità del browser richiedente e dispositivo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4746a-105">You can use the Browser property of the <xref:System.Web.HttpRequest> object to point to an instance of a <xref:System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities> object, which can then be used to read the capabilities of the requesting browser and device.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="4746a-106">Durante il caricamento della pagina, il <xref:System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities> oggetto Ottiene le funzionalità tramite il <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpCapabilitiesBase.Browser%2A> proprietà come spiegato in precedenza.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4746a-106">During the page load, the <xref:System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities> object obtains the capabilities through the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpCapabilitiesBase.Browser%2A> property as previously discussed.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="4746a-107">Il <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpCapabilitiesBase.PreferredRenderingMime%2A> e il <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpCapabilitiesBase.ScreenCharactersWidth%2A> proprietà del <xref:System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities> impostando le proprietà dell'oggetto report al browser il <xref:System.Web.HttpResponse> oggetto e anche impostando a livello di codice il `Text` proprietà di alcuni controlli della pagina.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4746a-107">The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpCapabilitiesBase.PreferredRenderingMime%2A> and the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpCapabilitiesBase.ScreenCharactersWidth%2A> properties of the <xref:System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities> object report back to the browser by setting properties on the <xref:System.Web.HttpResponse> object and also by programmatically setting the `Text` property of certain controls on the page.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
<%@ Page Inherits="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.MobilePage"   
    Language="c#" %>  
<script language="c#" runat="server">  
public void Page_Load(Object sender, EventArgs e)  
{  
    System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities currentCapabilities;  
    MobileCapabilities currentCapabilities =   
        (MobileCapabilities)Request.Browser;  
    // Programatically find the mobile capabilities without using   
    // DeviceSpecific Filters.  
    if(currentCapabilities.PreferredRenderingMIME=="text/html")  
    {  
        Label2.Text = "You are using an html supported device.";  
    }  
    else if(currentCapabilities.PreferredRenderingMIME ==   
        "text/vnd.wap.wml")  
    {  
        Label2.Text = "You are using a wml supported device.";  
    }  
    Label1.Text = "Screen Width (chars): " +   
        currentCapabilities.ScreenCharactersWidth;  
 }  
 </script>  
 <Mobile:Form runat="server" id=frmTemplate >  
      <mobile:label ID="Label1" runat="server" />  
      <mobile:label ID="Label2" runat="server" />  
 </Mobile:Form>  
```
